ABOUT

Visual audio mixer. The graphical representation of sounds brings concepts to audio that are traditionally more related to other fields, such as proximity, boundary, overlap and placing.

Based on my earlier work created with Director (2000), rewritten in C++ using OpenFrameworks.



USE

Build instructions for Mac OS X.

1. Get OpenFrameworks: http://openframeworks.cc/
2. Put the source code folder in your_openframeworks_folder/apps/some_folder/SoundField
3. Get the addons ofxDirList and ofxXmlSettings and put them in your_openframeworks_folder/addons/
4. Build and run the project from XCode
5. If all goes well you can play the distributed sound files


Playing sounds

1. Remove the distributed sound files in SoundField/bin/data/sounds and put your own. You can use audio files with format mp3/mp2/aiff/wav/ogg/raw
2. Delete the distributed settings file 'SoundFieldSettings' in SoundField/bin/data/settings/
3. Start SoundField
4. Save your settings by pressing 's'


Mouse

drag center: move sound
drag edge: shrink or expand sound
double click sound: toggle pause
double click walker: toggle pause


Keyboard 

s: Save settings in SoundField/bin/data/settings/SoundFieldSettings.xml (this overwrites the existing file)
f: toggle fullscreen
esc: quit



